# Spec Implementation — Modular Monorepo Structure

During **spec-to-deploy Stage 4** (and any feature work under `specs/NNN-*/`), place code in the owning service and preserve separation defined in `specs/monorepo-decomposition/`.

## Layout

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `apps/<service>/` | One deployable unit per directory (gateway, agent, workers, frontends) |
| `packages/<name>/` | Shared libraries only (`db`, `config`, `common`) — not feature logic |
| `tests/` | Cross-stack integration only; default unit tests live in the owning app |

## Before editing

1. Identify the **owning service** from `specs/monorepo-decomposition/02-app-inventory.md` and `specs/authoritative/<service>/`.
2. Confirm **call direction** in `04-dependency-graph.md` (e.g. frontends → APIs → workers → DB).
3. Split multi-service requirements into **one task per service**; note HTTP/Modal boundaries in the task list.

## Do

- Implement feature code inside the service that owns the data or runtime (Render vs Modal).
- Share cross-cutting code via `packages/` when 2+ services need it and the surface is stable (`10-shared-code-strategy.md`).
- Use **HTTP, OpenAPI, or Modal SDK** for cross-service behavior — not private imports across `apps/`.
- Colocate tests with the service (`apps/<svc>/tests/`, `apps/<svc>/src/`, frontend `tests/` or `e2e/`).
- Import `packages/db` models only for the **service’s own schema** at runtime.

## Do not

- Add business logic to `packages/` to avoid choosing a service owner.
- Import another app’s `src/` (e.g. `apps/gateway` importing `apps/agent/src/...`).
- Duplicate the same module in two apps instead of extracting to `packages/` (when extraction criteria in `10-shared-code-strategy.md` are met).
- Put gateway-only routing in workers, or worker/GPU logic in Render APIs, without an explicit spec-approved boundary change.

## Fuzzy boundaries — stop and ask

If the change touches **gateway vs agent**, **gateway vs data-management-api**, or adds a new shared package, stop and ask the user before proceeding (`ask-dont-assume`).

## Checklist (each implementation batch)

- [ ] Changes live under the correct `apps/<service>/` (or approved `packages/` extraction).
- [ ] No new cross-app Python/TS imports; inter-service calls use documented APIs.
- [ ] Matches `specs/NNN-*/` and authoritative service docs.
- [ ] Tests added in the owning service’s test tree.
